close_reason: "Fixed GH-485 by preserving search field:value tokens for the inline parser while keeping explicit flag precedence and docs/tests current; verified with focused tests, manual temp PM_PATH proof, full coverage, and CI static gates."
body: "## Reproduction (verified on 2026.7.9, local build)\n\n```bash\npm search \"status:all scene grounding\" --limit 5\n# Error: Missing required argument keywords\n# Recovery bundle shows: attempted_command: pm search --status \"all scene grounding\" --limit 5\n```\n\nThe inline-filter rewriter consumes everything after `status:` into the flag value instead of stopping at the first whitespace token boundary.\n\n## Impact\nBreaks the documented duplicate-check workflow (`pm search \"status:all <keywords>\"` before create) that agents use to avoid re-filing items. Workaround: pass `--status all` explicitly and keep keywords positional.\n\n## Upstream\nhttps://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/485 (filed 2026-07-08 by unbraind while implementing an all-status duplicate-check workflow).\n\n## Likely surface\nInline query-syntax parser from GH-157 remainder work (pm-ldr1) — the `status:`/`tag:` token rewrite path in search argument normalization."
